    "special": "",
    "notes": "<p>The universe can be counted. It all adds up and magic is no different. It’s not mystical, and doesn’t break any rules of physics, it’s just not well understood by the layman (and usually not by your typical mage either), and so is given a mythical status.</p><p>The Arithmomancer sees the esoteric formulae of magic for what they really are: A series of patterns and axioms used by charlatans, in secret cabals to obscure scientific advancement from the public at large in order to subjugate them.</p><p>Magic indeed.</p>",
